==Old English==
===Etymology===
From [[dreor|drēor]] + [[-ig|-iġ]].  Cognate with Old Saxon [[drorag|drōrag]] (Dutch [[treurig]]), Old High German [[trurag|trūrag]] (German [[traurig]]).

===Pronunciation===
[[IPA]]: /'dɹe:oɹɪj/

===Adjective===
'''drēoriġ'''
# [[bloody]], [[gory]]
#:''Wæter stod dreorig and gedrefed'': water stood gory and troubled.
# [[sad]], [[melancholy]]
#:''Hig wurdon swiðe dreorige'': they became very sad.

